OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1774246422
OL,3,CAround #1.8bn in business rates
OL,4,Cpredicted to be handed back to firms
OL,6,FAround #1.8 billion of business rates
OL,7,Fpayments are expected to be handed
OL,8,Fback to firms, according to Government
OL,9,Ffigures.
OL,11,FModelling by the Treasury has
OL,12,Findicated it expects significant
OL,13,Frebates in the face of changes to
OL,14,Fbusiness rates valuations, which are
OL,15,Fdue to take force at the start of the
OL,16,Fnew tax year in April.
OL,18,FThe figures were disclosed in official
OL,19,Fmodelling published under the Freedom
OL,20,Fof Information Act to global tax firm
OL,21,FRyan.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
